title: Contributing to sdtm.terminology
text: Fork package clone onto computer. haven’t done , recommend using usethis::create_from_github("patterninstitute/sdtm.terminology", fork = TRUE). Install development dependencies devtools::install_dev_deps(), make sure package passes R CMD check running devtools::check(). R CMD check doesn’t pass cleanly, ’s good idea ask help continuing. Create Git branch pull request (PR). recommend using usethis::pr_init("brief-description--change"). Make changes, commit git, create PR running usethis::pr_push(), following prompts browser. title PR briefly describe change. body PR contain Fixes #issue-number. user-facing changes, add bullet top NEWS.md (.e. just first header). Follow style described https://style.tidyverse.org/news.html.

title: CDISC SDTM Controlled Terminology
text: sdtm.terminology R data package providing CDISC SDTM terminology (release 2023-12-15). CDISC SDTM Controlled Terminology refers standardized set terms developed Clinical Data Interchange Standards Consortium (CDISC) specifically use Standard Data Tabulation Model (SDTM). Controlled terminology provides consistent vocabulary coding various types data collected clinical trials. standardization crucial ensuring data different studies, sponsors, sites can understood, compared, analyzed consistent manner. addition supplying SDTM terminology data, package includes several utility functions designed facilitate conversion codes terms, well verify association terms specific code lists.

title: CDISC SDTM Controlled Terminology
text: Convert terms codes codes terms, determine term included terminology code list:
code: # Convert a code list term to respective C-code and back again cl_term_to_code("UNIT") #> [1] "C71620" cl_code_to_term("C71620") #> [1] "UNIT"  # Are "%" and "%/s" terms from the UNIT code list? is_term(c("%", "%/s"), cl_term_to_code("UNIT")) #> [1] TRUE TRUE  # Find "%" and "%/s" codes within C71620 code list. term_to_code(c("%", "%/s"), "C71620") #> [1] "C25613"  "C163560"  # It seems "%" is also a term in the VSRESU code list but not "%/s". is_term(c("%", "%/s"), cl_term_to_code("VSRESU")) #> [1]  TRUE FALSE  # Or, equivalently, query using codes instead... is_code(c("C25613", "C163560"), cl_term_to_code("VSRESU")) #> [1]  TRUE FALSE  # Find which code lists contain the terms "DNA" or "RNA" match_code_list_from_term(c("DNA", "RNA")) #> # A tibble: 6 × 4 #>   code    term  cl_code cl_name                                  #>   <chr>   <chr> <chr>   <chr>                                    #> 1 C184459 DNA   C101832 Findings About Test Code                 #> 2 C449    DNA   C111114 Genetic Sample Type                      #> 3 C135409 DNA   C65047  Laboratory Test Code                     #> 4 C184459 DNA   C163027 Type 1 Diabetes Findings About Test Code #> 5 C812    RNA   C111114 Genetic Sample Type                      #> 6 C132301 RNA   C65047  Laboratory Test Code

title: CDISC SDTM Controlled Terminology
text: sdtm.terminology bundles three data sets: sdtm_terminology: data set provided upstream CDISC, except variable renaming conversion “Yes”/“” values TRUE/FALSE values is_extensible column. sdtm_code_lists: subset sdtm_terminology containing code lists. sdtm_code_terms: subset sdtm_terminology containing terms code lists.

what: SDTM codelist code to term — cl_code_to_term
title: SDTM codelist code to term — cl_code_to_term
text: cl_code_to_term() maps SDTM terminology codelists' C-codes respective terms. mapping codes representing codelists, use code_to_term() instead.

title: SDTM codelist code to term — cl_code_to_term
SDTM codelist code to term — cl_code_to_term
text: code C-code leading character C followed sequence digits used uniquely identifying SDTM terminology codelist.

title: SDTM codelist code to term — cl_code_to_term
text: character vector SDTM terms codelists. number elements returned matches number elements code, .e. one--one correspondence input output. Invalid codes code mapped NA.

title: SDTM codelist code to term — cl_code_to_term
code: cl_code_to_term(code = "C66731") #> [1] "SEX"  # `code` is vectorized. cl_code_to_term(code = c("C66731", "C66733")) #> [1] "SEX"  "SIZE"  # Invalid codes (e.g. `"YODA"`) map to `NA`. cl_code_to_term(code = c("C66731", "C66733", "C007")) #> [1] "SEX"  "SIZE" NA

title: SDTM codelist term to code — cl_term_to_code

title: SDTM codelist term to code — cl_term_to_code
SDTM codelist term to code — cl_term_to_code
text: term SDTM controlled terminology term referring codelist.

title: SDTM codelist term to code — cl_term_to_code
text: character vector SDTM codes codelists. number elements returned matches number elements term, .e. one--one correspondence input output. Invalid codes term mapped NA.

title: SDTM codelist term to code — cl_term_to_code
code: cl_term_to_code(term = "SEX") #> [1] "C66731"  # `term` is vectorized. cl_term_to_code(term = c("SEX", "SIZE")) #> [1] "C66731" "C66733"  # Invalid codes (e.g. `"YODA"`) map to `NA`. cl_term_to_code(term = c("SEX", "SIZE", "YODA")) #> [1] "C66731" "C66733" NA

title: SDTM code to term — code_to_term
text: code_to_term() maps SDTM terminology C-codes respective terms. mapping codes representing codelists, use cl_code_to_term() instead.

title: SDTM code to term — code_to_term
text: code C-code leading character C followed sequence digits used uniquely identifying concept NCI Thesaurus (NCIt), including CDISC concepts. code_list Parent codelist code.

title: SDTM code to term — code_to_term
text: character vector SDTM controlled terminology terms. number elements returned matches number elements code, .e. one--one correspondence input output. Invalid codes code mapped NA.

title: SDTM code to term — code_to_term
code: code_to_term(code = "C174106", code_list = "C141657") #> [1] "TENMW101"  # Both `code` and `code_list` are vectorized. `code_list` will be recycled # to match `code` number of elements. code_to_term(code = c("C174106", "C141700"), code_list = "C141657") #> [1] "TENMW101" "TENMW102"  # You may mix codelists as long as `code` and `code_list` have the same # number of elements; they will be matched element-wise. code_to_term(   code = c("C174106", "C141700", "C141701"),   code_list = c("C141657", "C141657", "C141656") ) #> [1] "TENMW101"          "TENMW102"          "TENMW1-Test Grade"  # Invalid codes (e.g. `"C00000"`) map to `NA`. code_to_term(code = c("C174106", "C141700", "C00000"), code_list = "C141657") #> [1] "TENMW101" "TENMW102" NA

what: Is a code or term in a codelist? — is_term
title: Is a code or term in a codelist? — is_term
text: is_code() is_term() evaluate whether query codes terms part SDTM controlled terminology within context codelist.

title: Is a code or term in a codelist? — is_term
Is a code or term in a codelist? — is_term
text: term character vector terms (e.g. "TENMW102"). codelist character vector codes referring SDTM terminology codelists (e.g. "C141657"). code character vector C-codes (e.g. "C174106").

title: Is a code or term in a codelist? — is_term
text: logical vector, TRUE indicates term controlled terminology term within codelist provided, FALSE, otherwise.

title: Is a code or term in a codelist? — is_term
code: is_term(term = "TENMW101", codelist = "C141657") #> [1] TRUE  # Note that the codelist term itself (`"TENMW1TC"`) is not part of its own # codelist (`"C141657"`). is_term(term = "TENMW1TC", codelist = "C141657") #> [1] FALSE  # `is_term()` is vectorized over `term` and `codelist` is_term(term = c("TENMW101", "TENMW104"), codelist = "C141657") #> [1] TRUE TRUE  is_code(code = "C174106", codelist = "C141657") #> [1] TRUE  # Note that the codelist code itself (`"C141657"`) is not part of its own # codelist (`"C141657"`). is_code(code = "C141657", codelist = "C141657") #> [1] FALSE  # `is_code()` is vectorized over `code` and `codelist` is_code(code = c("C174106", "C141701"), codelist = "C141657") #> [1] TRUE TRUE

title: Match code lists — match_code_list_from_term
text: match_code_list_from_term() takes terms queries look associated code lists. match_code_list_from_code() starting C-codes. Note mappings potentially one many code term may associate one code list.

title: Match code lists — match_code_list_from_term
text: term character vector SDTM terminology terms. code character vector SDTM terminology C-codes.

title: Match code lists — match_code_list_from_term
text: tibble least many rows elements term, potentially one--many mappings. returned tibble comprises three columns: term SDTM terminology term (e.g. "TENMW104"). code SDTM terminology code (e.g. "C141701"). cl_code code associated code list. cl_name name associated code list.

title: Match code lists — match_code_list_from_term
code: # Find code lists where "DNA" and "RNA" are used. match_code_list_from_term(c("DNA", "RNA")) #> # A tibble: 6 × 4 #>   code    term  cl_code cl_name                                  #>   <chr>   <chr> <chr>   <chr>                                    #> 1 C184459 DNA   C101832 Findings About Test Code                 #> 2 C449    DNA   C111114 Genetic Sample Type                      #> 3 C135409 DNA   C65047  Laboratory Test Code                     #> 4 C184459 DNA   C163027 Type 1 Diabetes Findings About Test Code #> 5 C812    RNA   C111114 Genetic Sample Type                      #> 6 C132301 RNA   C65047  Laboratory Test Code                      # Find code lists where "Yes"/"No" terms are controlled vocabulary. match_code_list_from_term(c("Yes", "No")) #> # A tibble: 6 × 4 #>   code    term  cl_code cl_name                                                  #>   <chr>   <chr> <chr>   <chr>                                                    #> 1 C182703 Yes   C182467 Abnormal Involuntary Movement Scale Clinical Classifica… #> 2 C182745 Yes   C182471 ATLAS Clinical Classification ORRES for ATLAS102 TN/TC   #> 3 C182702 No    C182467 Abnormal Involuntary Movement Scale Clinical Classifica… #> 4 C182744 No    C182471 ATLAS Clinical Classification ORRES for ATLAS102 TN/TC   #> 5 C180261 No    C179945 Combat Exposure Scale Questionnaire ORRES for CES0101 T… #> 6 C180271 No    C179947 Combat Exposure Scale Questionnaire ORRES for CES0103 T…  # C163560 is found in code list C71620. match_code_list_from_code("C163560") #> # A tibble: 1 × 4 #>   code    term  cl_code cl_name #>   <chr>   <chr> <chr>   <chr>   #> 1 C163560 %/s   C71620  Unit     # C25613 however is mapped to many code lists. match_code_list_from_code("C25613") #> # A tibble: 3 × 4 #>   code   term  cl_code cl_name                       #>   <chr>  <chr> <chr>   <chr>                         #> 1 C25613 %     C85494  PK Units of Measure           #> 2 C25613 %     C71620  Unit                          #> 3 C25613 %     C66770  Units for Vital Signs Results  # Unmappable codes or terms map to `NA`. match_code_list_from_code("Yoda") #> # A tibble: 1 × 4 #>   code  term  cl_code cl_name #>   <chr> <chr> <chr>   <chr>   #> 1 Yoda  NA    NA      NA      match_code_list_from_term("R2D2") #> # A tibble: 1 × 4 #>   code  term  cl_code cl_name #>   <chr> <chr> <chr>   <chr>   #> 1 NA    R2D2  NA      NA       # Codes for code lists are for all intents and purposes not mappable to # parent code lists. "C141657" %in% cl_codes() # C141657 is a code list #> [1] TRUE match_code_list_from_code(code = "C141657") #> # A tibble: 1 × 4 #>   code    term  cl_code cl_name #>   <chr>   <chr> <chr>   <chr>   #> 1 C141657 NA    NA      NA

title: SDTM code lists — sdtm_code_lists
text: tibble providing data set controlled terms SDTM code lists. code C-code leading character C followed sequence digits used uniquely identifying concept NCI Thesaurus (NCIt), including CDISC concepts. term specific value expected submissions. is_extensible Defines controlled terms may added codelist. New terms may added existing codelist values codelist value TRUE long terms duplicates synonyms existing terms. expectation sponsors use published controlled terminology standard baseline codelists defined extensible may terms added sponsor internally.  codelists FALSE sponsor organizations may add published lists. Suggestions new terms may requested New Term Request Page. cl_name Contains descriptive name codelist. synonym identifies applicable synonyms CDISC submission value indicated column term. terms submitted, included collection mapping purposes. Note: especially important instances test name parameter test name contains corresponding test code parameter test code. definition identifies value ALT_DEFINITION property CDISC source particular concept. many cases existing NCI definition used. source definition noted parentheses (e.g. NCI, CDISC glossary). nci_term identifies value PREFERRED_NAME property concept NCIt. column designates human readable, fully specified preferred term corresponding NCI C-code, especially helpful searching NCIt get entire concept links instances term.

title: SDTM term to code — term_to_code
text: term_to_code() maps SDTM terminology terms respective C-codes. mapping terms referring codelists, use cl_term_to_code() instead.

title: SDTM term to code — term_to_code
text: term SDTM controlled terminology term (expected submissions). code_list Parent codelist code.

text: character vector SDTM controlled terminology C-codes. number elements returned matches number elements term, .e. one--one correspondence input output. Invalid codes term mapped NA.

title: SDTM term to code — term_to_code
code: term_to_code(term = "TENMW101", code_list = "C141657") #> [1] "C174106"  # Both `term` and `code_list` are vectorized. `code_list` will be recycled # to match `term` number of elements. term_to_code(term = c("TENMW101", "TENMW102"), code_list = "C141657") #> [1] "C174106" "C141700"  # You may mix codelists as long as `term` and `code_list` have the same # number of elements; they will be matched element-wise. term_to_code(   term = c("TENMW101", "TENMW102", "TENMW1-Test Grade"),   code_list = c("C141657", "C141657", "C141656") ) #> [1] "C174106" "C141700" "C141701"  # Invalid terms (e.g. `"Gambelas"`) map to `NA`. term_to_code(term = c("TENMW101", "TENMW102", "Gambelas"), code_list = "C141657") #> [1] "C174106" "C141700" NA
